`IFormFile` buffers into memory by default — for large files you need to read the raw request body stream instead.

**Key changes:**

```csharp
// Program.cs
// 1. Raise the max request body size
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(k =>
    k.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024); // 2 GB

// 2. Stream directly to disk from the request body
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Disable form buffering for this endpoint
    if (!request.HasFormContentType)
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected multipart/form-data");

    var boundary = request.GetMultipartBoundary();
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(boundary))
        return Results.BadRequest("Missing boundary");

    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);
    MultipartSection? section;

    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var cd) || !cd.IsFileDisposition())
            continue;

        var fileName = Path.GetRandomFileName(); // safe name
        var path = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

        await using var fs = File.Create(path);
        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs);       // streams in chunks, ~80 KB

        return Results.Ok(new { saved = fileName });
    }

    return Results.BadRequest("No file found");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // required for minimal API form uploads
```

**Required using:**
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities;   // MultipartReader
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;          // ContentDispositionHeaderValue
```

**Why this works:**

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Memory | Buffers entire file | Streams in small chunks |
| 2 GB file | OOM crash | ~80 KB peak allocation |

**Other things to wire up:**

- **Request timeout** — large uploads over slow links need longer than the 30 s default:
  ```csharp
  .WithMetadata(new RequestTimeoutAttribute(600_000)) // 10 min
  ```
- **Reverse proxy limits** — if behind Nginx/APIGW, raise `client_max_body_size` or equivalent there too.
- **Progress / cancellation** — pass a `CancellationToken` to `CopyToAsync` and use `request.HttpContext.RequestAborted`.
